or=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ularcenmistwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Larcen Mistwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 3:39:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> This won't give you 60kpp either, but is also a good way to make money at the low levels.  All you need is a rogue with a hide/sneak skill ( sometimes takes until level 4 for some races ).  Kill bears and get a HQ Bearskin, to sell for 30pp ( or more if you're lucky ).  Head down into lower guk and auction that you are buying FS Weapons for 2pp each.  They sell at a merchant for 4-6pp depending on weapon, faction and charisma.  Rinse and repeat, carrying as many weapons as you can and still be able to move.  Mostly though I wouldn't worry about money.  I've never had more that 10kpp at a time, and I can still contribute greatly to groups and raids.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 3:50:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> Fine, you want a relevant example?<br>
<br>
Just today I was told that I (as a Paladin) shouldn't try buying or getting a Centi Longsword... because classes that can Dual Wield will do more damage with them.<br>
<br>
So if my Paladin goes on a camp for a Lammy... or even worse, my Cleric gets invited to an area that has great drops for Melee weapons... I should just sit there and be quiet.  I don't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> deserve</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to roll on items that I could sell to buy the items I need.<br>
<br>
Oh, and another thing...  When you pull the NBG card, do you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ever</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> offer to random off the item you're replacing?  (assuming it's not a No Drop item.)<br>
<br>
If you're after a specific item, then you should get your friends to help you.  If you're in a true pick-up group, then you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> expect that everyone will want to have the same chance to make a profit from the drops. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualferogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alfe Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 3:58:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> wow Angelsyn I never even thought about rolling on the item they are replacing, that is a good point you make i will have to bring that up next time someone raises the NBG card thx =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 4:21:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> money</span><hr size=1> Best way to make money in the game is NOT from overpopulated dungeons like Seb/KC ect. <br>
<br>
To make a lot of money fast, first you need a group of players with actual skill. This allows you to accomplish things with less people than others, hence more loot for each person. Pickup groups simply don't work for this.<br>
<br>
Now, goto a dungeon or a zone that either is not overpopulated, OR go deep into that zone where no one but guilds go. For instance, a group of 6 of us would camp/farm the velks castle right after the zone was upgraded. Farming barbed ringmail / blood-runed armor when there were only a couple of pieces in existance gave us all a lot of cash. I scored the first pair of blood runed legs after the upgrade... after a bit of asking around, i got a total of 225k for them. The rest of the people in the group eventually got a few pieces each, and the total amount of plat made per person evened out.<br>
<br>
After that we moved on to HoT, still with the 6 man group. We all got full suits of armor, and stayed around to aqquire more which we sold off for yet more plat.<br>
<br>
Summary : the trick of making a lot of plat from non-trading is to go places normal pickup groups can't go. You'll get the items that are more rare, and hence sell for more plat.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 6:43:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> Actually, I almost always do that.<br>
<br>
When I was teamed up with a Ranger hunting rare stuff in Twilight Sea, we looted a Lesser Guard of Haste.  I won the roll, so I gave him my Seb Scale Mantle because it was an upgrade for him. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upyrhos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pyrhos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/7/02 7:17:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> I solo dragons. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulomack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lomack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/02 1:08:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> I've made quite a few k plat recently just doing faction work.  I killed the zillion goblins in Drogna necessary to get my faction from max kos to max ally with DiZok.  In the process I managed to make 5k+. Im almost positive I made more than 5k, just using that as a base number.  I never left the place to sell stuff, but I sure never left without all my packs totally filled.  I did leave to raid and xp, just did this during free time over the past few weeks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uturlo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Turlo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/02 5:06:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> I just bought my 103k horse (which I love).  How did I get it?  First step, I performed spring cleaning on all my alts, and had a field day at auction.  65k right there.  Then I sold all of my tinkerer bags at cost to players.  Up to 100k there.  Then, it was a question of 2200pp i was short.  The guild didn't want me to sell any of my dagger collection, so they spotted me the difference.<br>
<br>
It was strange...I was asking myself stuff like..When did I get a Defiance?  Etc.  I did all this without stripping a single alt.  Is this advice useful?  Probably not.  But I am a 56 rogue that saves every copper and picks up fishing grubs.  Save everything!  It was amazing what I had stacked up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uclammorsz1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clammor SZ1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/02 8:08:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> soloing dragons doesn't tend to be good cash, just bad faction =( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/8/02 8:54:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10167.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: erm...</span><hr size=1> If your solo'ing WW dragons, you can sell off the dragon armor for a LOT.  And if you are good enough to pick off a Kunark dragon solo, thats great money right there.  CoF are still dragon haste and still worth alot.  Also, if you can solo phin (I know shaman can do it.  I'd think necros or mages could, and I know a druid that almost did it until charm on the seahorse was dispelled.<br>
<br>
I think there are 3 standard ways of making money though:<br>
